reviewText: The premise is good, but the show itself is very slow. Excruciatingly slow
Not a bad movie, give great insight of how football is played in the state of Mississippi for junior college.
To dang slow, cheesy, I didn't like it and I like anything that has to do with football..
Not very interesting. I couldn't even finish it. The attempt at humor by having the mascots trying to do silly things was just ridiculous.
IT OUTLINE THE PRINCIPAL OF THE GAME AND THE REQUIREMENT TO BE THE BEST AS A PLAYER AND TEAM WITH SPORTSMANSHIP.
This is more of a promotional video for the schools with a focus on football. Not a great film, very repetitive
loved it - kick ass football like it should be
It was a good overall view of junior college football in Missississippi. There was not as much history in the video as I thought there would be.

This is just a promotional video for the JUCO league in Mississippi and their junior colleges. I have seen harder hits on Kenny Chesneys documentary "boys of fall", so this doesn't really look like the toughest league in America. Though still it is quite ok and gives you a feeling for the tradition of those junior colleges. It's nice to watch, but you don't miss something, if you don't see it.
Couldn't get past the 1960s era narration.  Just didn't fit at all.
Just plain bad.  Don't waste your time even reading the description.
Last Chance U must have learned their lesson from this awful documentary. I couldn't finish watching this

Literally one of the most boring things I've ever watched. The idea behind it is solid. The football looks good. But it took almost 28 minutes before you see any game film. Plus the announcer on the game film was horrible. The narrator sounded like he was from 1980's documentaries. Again, great idea, really rough output.
It was ok.  It was a little bit longer than it it probably needed to be, but had some interesting points about JUCO football.
Real life football and home town support
Good but not great; slow and somewhat predictable.
Decent clip

Quaint and starts off nice as a historical look at the league but in an effort to give each school it's own time, the film drags on.  Each highlight of a school starts to bleed together. Would've been better if it were about an hour shorter.
This is a 2 hour documentary of people talking. Boring
They wasted 9 min for an introduction of useless video footage!

Way too many B-reels to be considered a full featured documentary film! No plot, no interviews worth mentioning. All around horrible structure and format. This video gives low-budget a bad name! Even at the free price tag, this video is too expensive. A waste of life and phone battery (viewed via Amazon Video app.)
Not much football insight, mostly filler. However, the cowbells in the music for the actual games is fantastic!
Loved it!

Great discovery. I didn't know about this football system. The players and fans are awesome. The story telling got long winded at times. It could have been shorter or better yet done in episodes to provide more specific information on all the JUCOS.
I thought it was a very good film ... To see what these young men go through to make it to the nfl
After watching Last Chance U, i really couldn't get into this.

Absolutely all over the place film...very basic quality....but redeemed by the behind the scenes look...when It does actually talk about the football.  Definitely could have used some serious editing.
Trash
some the film seem a Lil blurry
Provides an inside look at all the wannabes that didn't make it or couldn't cut it at the big time college football programs, and how spoiled many of them are with little interest in education
Not much of a story here just a glimpse of the league in general.
great coach

If you want to see a series about how tough JUCO football is in Mississippi, watch Last Chance U on Netflix.  It follows East Mississippi Community College and it depicts how rough football is down there.
It wasn't a documentary, it was a promotional film for Mississippi JC Football.
Unfortunately I'd just finished watching the Amazon/HBO series All Or Nothing about the NFL. Juco couldn't compare.
Boring
The narrator is awful i couldn't watch the whole thing because of that guy's voice

Of course, I love this because it is about Mississippi junior college football. I love the term "juco".  For the last couple of years I have grown more interested in junior college football because we have such good players on that level. I have been following it because it is fascinating. This documentary open my eyes as to why.  Very interesting!

Very informative, however could have been filmed better.

Honestly the worst documentary I have watched in a long time. Almost no storyline. Very little football.

If you aren't an alumni of a Mississippi Juno, this will bore you times ten.

Interesting story about JUCO football. Worth watching if you'received a football fan. A little slow and repetitive.  A lot of players have been developed in the JUCO circuit.
